Dictionary.Name: The Collaborative International Dictionary of English v.0.44

Definition.WordDefinition:
L \L\, a. 1. Having the general shape of the (capital) letter L; as, an L beam, or L-beam. [Webster 1913 Suppl.]
2. Elevated; -- a symbol for {el.} as an abbreviation of elevated in elevated road or railroad. -- n. An elevated road; as, to ride on the L. [Colloq., U. S.] [Webster 1913 Suppl.]

Definition.WordDefinition: EL n 1: angular distance above the horizon (especially of a celestial object) [syn: {elevation}, {altitude}, {ALT}] 2: an electric elevated railway [syn: {elevated railway}, {elevated railroad}, {overhead railway}]
